---
import logoBostonTSClub from "~/assets/logos/boston-ts-club.png";
import logoMichiganTypeScript from "~/assets/logos/michigan-typescript.png";
import stillOrganizersHugging from "~/assets/stills/organizers-hugging.png";

import BodyText from "./BodyText.astro";
import EmphasizedText from "./EmphasizedText.astro";
import ImagesAndTextTwoColumn from "./ImagesAndTextTwoColumn.astro";
---

<ImagesAndTextTwoColumn
	heading="About us"
	images={{
		primary: stillOrganizersHugging,
		secondary: [
			{
				alt: "Michigan TypeScript logo",
				height: "120",
				src: logoMichiganTypeScript,
			},
			{
				alt: "Boston TS Club logo",
				height: "120",
				src: logoBostonTSClub,
			},
		],
	}}
>
	<BodyText class="about-us-body-text">
		SquiggleConf brings web developers together to learn, share, and grow.
	</BodyText>

	<BodyText class="about-us-body-text">
		As a program of Squiggle.Tools, a nonprofit organization, we foster
		community not just at our annual conference, but year-round through
		<EmphasizedText
			><a href="https://bostonts.club" target="_blank">Boston TS Club</a
			></EmphasizedText
		>
		and
		<EmphasizedText
			><a href="https://michigantypescript.com" target="_blank"
				>Michigan TypeScript</a
			></EmphasizedText
		>.
	</BodyText>

	<BodyText class="about-us-body-text">
		We believe tech education should be accessible to all. Each year around
		SquiggleConf, we organize volunteering initiatives such as teaching local
		teens to code. And while SquiggleConf tickets have a cost, we offer multiple
		paths to attend for free or at a discount.
	</BodyText>

	<BodyText class="about-us-body-text">
		SquiggleConf strives to create an inclusive conference that welcomes
		developers from every background- no matter your age, skill level, or career
		path.
	</BodyText>
</ImagesAndTextTwoColumn>

<style>
	.about-us-body-text {
		font-size: var(--fontSizeSmall);
	}

	.about-us-body-text + .about-us-body-text {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}
</style>
